"Prison overpopulation," and the article it links to, prison overcrowding, is not an accurate description of what the song criticizes. Prison overcrowding refers to the idea of too many people bunched up in one place in the prison and not enough resources to take care of them. While this is a consequence of mass incarceration, the problems implied in the term "prison overcrowding" are not the issues referred to in the song.
